Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{3}(no need to peel!) into 2cm chunks. Pop your potatoes into your pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. We will add the cabbage for the final 5 mins. Tip: The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them. When done, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Meanwhile, place the @pork and oregano sausages{4} on an oiled #baking tray{} and put them on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through to make sure they cook evenly.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Pour the boiling @water{50%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock powder{0.5%tsp} and the @apple and sage jelly{2}. Stir until dissolved. Quarter the @apple{1}(no need to peel) and remove the core. Cut each quarter in half.

Melt half the @unsalted butter{30%g} in a #frying pan{} over medium-low heat. Add the apple and @dried thyme{1} and cook until the apple is browned all over, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every minute or so to make sure it colours evenly. Pour in the jelly stock mixture and increase heat to medium. Simmer until the apple is soft and the sauce is glossy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Lower the heat and keep warm until you are ready to serve.

> Tip: If your sauce reduces too much, simply add a splash of water to loosen it up.

When the potatoes have 5 minutes cooking time left, add the @shredded savoy cabbage{150%g} to the potato pan and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. When the potato and greens are ready, drain and roughly mash them together with the remaining butter. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve the sausages with the mash and glazed apple sauce. Enjoy!